Did you we are a Lennox dealer?  #lennoxstrong We go out of our way to find the best brands available that offer the best warranty/quality available to save you from having to do that research, you are in great hands when you call us !

We are very honoured that Rogers Media did this video of our company sharing how much we care about our clients feel free to copy and paste this link - https://www.facebook.com/RogersForBusiness/posts/1526593684061732 
 
As an owner-operated local company that has been in business for over 16 years, we are proud to accept Homestars ˜Best of” Award for 8 consecutive years in a row. Here’s to a great year, and many more to come.
 
Starting in the trade in 1995 and working the different sectors learning some amazing experiences while taking annual courses to learn each manufacture James Smith created Natural Choice Heating & Cooling with two things in mind, caring for the client and caring about the employee.  With those in mind was the inception and created over a decade and half of the highest quality of workmanship and we rolled out our red carpet treatment.  Each employee proudly takes pictures of every installation from a thermostat to full custom ductwork installations, no project is too little.   Our team of 10 well trained techs are willing and ready to take on any project you have.
 
Here at Natural Choice Heating & Cooling it has been our pleasure to offer the highest level of reliable comfort control for the Whitby, Durham, GTA, Kawartha Lakes & surrounding community for over a decade and half. Our foundation consists of efficient, reliable and cost effective heating, furnace, air conditioning, tankless and indoor air quality products.  Along with ductless systems offered in Heat Pumps by different manufactures include Mitsubishi, Fujitsu, Samsung & LG's Art Cool system.  We are also a leader in tankless systems installing Rinnai's for over a decade and half as an Authorized Service Provider for Rinnai.
 
From start to finish, our experienced estimators, project managers and technicians provide the expertise to ensure your project is completed on time, on budget and up to code. We understand that service interruptions are an inconvenience and cost you productivity so we focus on providing expedient services to get you back online as soon as possible without risking the safety of your valuable equipment. We are also absolutely committed to safety and provide ongoing education to our personnel to ensure complete compliance with the best practices and standards.
 
We offer our services to the following areas - Markham, Uxbridge, Richmond Hill, Scarborough, Cobourg, Port Hope, Unionville, Vaughan, Port Perry, Pickering, Ajax, Whitby, Oshawa, Courtice, Bowmanville, Lindsay, Peterborough

profile:
Heating and Cooling is what we do, but family is at the heart of who we are. For more than 13 years, we haven’t just been your trusted comfort partner; we’ve been the Ashton Family business.  Priding ourselves on prompt, professional service, we work hard to give you and your family the value and quality that you deserve. 

We offer no cost, no pressure in home consultations to answer all of your questions about purchasing new appliances like furnaces, air conditioners, fireplaces and more. You can breathe easy with a detailed duct cleaning service, or talk to a comfort advisor about how you can reduce dust, eliminate cold rooms and save money with the Aeroseal Duct Sealing process that seals your ducts from the inside.

Don’t wait days for service, or wait on hold for hours, and enjoy a variety of flexible payment options, including financing, that make doing business with us easy. We even offer monthly maintenance and protection plans for your appliances so you can stop worrying about surprise repair bills. Hey- that’s what family is for, right? 

Contact us today and let us help you Be More Comfortable.

profile:
Canadian Gas Service is an experienced, knowledgeable, reliable, certified and insured natural gas and propane fitter, registered with the Technical Standards & Safety Authority since 2002. We specializes in the installation, maintenance and repair, of natural gas pipelines, furnaces, and appliances for residences, commercial enterprises, institutions and industry. CGS crews specialize in gas leak detection in gas lines, using 21st century technology. 

Appliance and gas line installations are completed according to specifications and Canadian Standards by friendly, knowledgeable crews who respond quickly to service calls, while educating clients about their purchase. Certified installation crews focus above all else on the safety of their customers and a safe workplace environment. Crews take personal pride in every installation using natural gas and electricity.

Natural gas installations—including underground
Canadian Gas Service installs and modifies all types of natural gas piping for residences, commercial enterprises, institutions and industry:
    Underground applications
    Iron piping and flexible steel piping
    Leak detection and repair
    Installation of restaurant equipment
    Dishwashers
    Over the range microwaves
    Wall ovens
    Icemakers/Waterlines
    Natural gas ranges
    Cooktops
    Barbeques
    Washers and dryers
    Range hoods

All appliances installation:
Canadian Gas Service installs all types of residential appliances in a timely manner. Routinely-installed brands include Bosch, Kitchen Aid, Whirlpool, Maytag, Electrolux, Fisher Paykel, Miele, Samsung, Life’s Good (LG), and General Electric (GE).

Water heater sales, installation and service:
CGS representatives make site visits to work with people who have questions and concerns about the options available for heating water. They review the fundamentals of any system such as energy conservation, demand, space optimization, and health and safety to the occupants. The consultation is free and available within 24 hours of receiving a request for this service.

CGS is an authorized GSW Dealer.  The company has access to the latest in technology and has taken great care in determining what product lines are best for customers.

Tankless water heaters supplied by Takagi  is an example of smart technologies that are growing in demand.

CGS helps determine if a tankless system is right for a residence or business. This service is free. CGS wants customers to be totally comfortable with a product or service before a decision is made.

Furnaces sales, installation and service:
When searching for a new central heating system or when an  old furnace is not working properly, call Canadian Gas Service. CGS offers 24-hour emergency service, with service vehicles located throughout Halton and Peel Regions. CGS crews are experienced in the service and repair of all major brands of gas furnaces and central heating systems for residential, commercial, institutional and industrial heating and air conditioning equipment.

Natural gas leak detection and repair:
Natural gas and propane pipelines, equipment and appliances should be inspected for maintenance every two years or immediately following home improvements or reconstruction. Safety concerns range from asphyxiation to fire, and gas leaks have an immediate impact on the cost of fuel.

Homeowners, business execs and plant managers can contribute to the reduction of greenhouse gas emissions and a healthier natural environment by maintaining natural gas and propane systems regularly. Controlling GHG emissions leads to health, safety, environmental and economic benefits.

Garage heating systems:
Garage gas heaters make the workplace more useful and comfortable. In Canada, natural gas heaters are needed towork year-round. The most efficient system is usually a gas-fired, forced-air unit heater. Portable kerosene or propane heaters require ventilation, adding to the system complexity and safety considerations. 

Restaurant natural gas systems:
Natural gas is a popular choice for restaurants and other establishments that require cooking facilities including natural gas-fired fryers, griddles, ovens, and hot and cold storage areas. A natural gas system is economical, dependable and easy to use. Heating a restaurant with natural gas provides comfort to customers and saves money. Grills, deep fryers and exhaust systems, however, present a fire risk if not properly cleaned and maintained. Regular inspections by a CGS crew will reduce risks and show where efficiencies may be found.

The natural gas industry has transformed into one of the most technologically advanced industries. Natural gas appliances are also rising in popularity due to their efficiency and cost effectiveness. Although many natural gas-powered appliances are initially more expensive than their electric counterparts, they are commonly much cheaper to operate, have a longer expected life, and require relatively low maintenance. Other natural gas appliances include generators, space heaters, clothes dryers, pool and jacuzzi heaters, indoor and outdoor fireplaces, barbecues, garage heaters and outdoor heaters and lights. All of these appliances offer a safe, efficient, and economical alternative to electricity or other fuel sources. The same natural gas pipes that supply gas to a furnace can be used to supply energy for all of the appliances listed above, making installation simple and easy.

Natural gas fuel cells and microturbines both offer the residential consumer the capacity to disconnect from their local electric distributor, and generate just enough electricity to meet their needs. Although this technology is still in its infancy, it is very promising in being able to offer independent, reliable, efficient, environmentally-friendly electricity for residential needs

specialities:
How does the homeowner get emergency gas service immediately?
Only in emergency situations call your local gas supplier. They will not repair anything on the outlet side of the gas meter. They will, however, shut the house down if a dangerous situation is present. You must call a TSSA-registered company such as Canadian Gas Service to make necessary alterations, or repairs to your natural gas system.
